#Text=I ’m very proud of that .
#Text=And I 'm proud of the fact that the folks in Zionsville took the ball and ran with it .
#Text=I was honored to work with then state representative Jim Buck , from Kokomo , who also represented Zionsville .
#Text=And I represented ... at the time , not Zionsville .
#Text=It was n't until afterwards that Zionsville became part of my area .
#Text=Here is one other neat story .
#Text=The Town Hall chambers in Zionsville is the former Methodist church where Beth and I got married in .
#Text=When we had this ceremony of this dissolution of Eagle and Union Townships and the creation of the new town of Zionsville .
#Text=It literally happened right where we got married .
#Text=And I was asked to speak right in the same place where I exchanged my wedding vows with my wife .
#Text=I got up to speak and I was nervous and stammering a little bit and they 're like " Senator is everything ok ? "
#Text=And I 'm like , " For some reason , this specific location in the world , I 'm in a vortex , and it makes me really nervous . "
#Text=Tew : Thank you , senator .
#Text=And , let 's pause for identification .
#Text=Interview ( part IV ) :
#Text=Conclusion
#Text=This is Wikinews , and we are back with Senator Mike Delph .
#Text=I am Chad Tew , and we are here at The Edge radio studios with my journalism students and recording from the campus of the University of Southern Indiana , in Evansville .
#Text=Our first question will come from Jordan .
#Text=Jordan Bayes : Hi , Senator Delph , Jordan Bayes speaking .
#Text=What ever became of the military investigation of you and the soldier who appeared by you at a press conference ?
#Text=Well that was ultimately adjudicated by the military .
#Text=Colonel Mejia ended up retiring in good standing with the military .
#Text=At the time I was a captain in the United States Army Reserve , and I am now a major .
#Text=So I think everybody has moved forward and moved on .
#Text=Tew :
#Text=And you were never punished for that , for the record ?
#Text=There was a resolution that I had with my commanding general that is private , but there was never anything official other than on my officer evaluation report that denoted the issue .
#Text=Tew :
#Text=Yes , and then you were successfully promoted .

#Text=Successfully promoted for major and more importantly I get , I wo n't say harassed , but a fair number of calls from recruitment and retention people asking me to take leadership of units and to be more involved in the military , as if I have all this extra time on my hands .
#Text=But let me just tell you , on that whole deal .
#Text=I do n't go through life with regrets .
#Text=I had no regrets for that press conference .

#Text=The purpose of that press conference was to show Ray Mejia to the world , and how a guy who came from Mexico , not knowing the language , not being a citizen , used the path of the military to rise up through the ranks , get an education , learn the English language , and then ultimately become a successful executive with Eli Lilly .
#Text=To me that was a story that needed to be told .
#Text=Nobody was telling it .
#Text=Ray Mejia is very proud of his military service , as am I , and he wanted to show off what he had done in the military that was part of his identity and part of his story .
